<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17521026-48">
               <interp inst="t17521026-48" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17521026-48" type="year" value="1752"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17521026-48" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17521026"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17521026-48" type="date" value="17521026"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17521026-48-off247-c324" targOrder="Y" targets="t17521026-48-defend410 t17521026-48-off247 t17521026-48-verdict251"></join>
         
               <p>552. (M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17521026-48-defend410" type="defendantName">
                     Lewis 
                     Lewis 
                  <interp inst="t17521026-48-defend410" type="surname" value="Lewis"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17521026-48-defend410" type="given" value="Lewis"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17521026-48-defend410" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for that <rs id="t17521026-48-off247" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17521026-48-off247" type="offenceCategory" value="violentTheft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17521026-48-off247" type="offenceSubcategory" value="highwayRobbery"></interp>
               he, on the king's highway, on 
                     
                        <persName id="t17521026-48-victim412" type="victimName">
                           Ann 
                           Howard 
                        <interp inst="t17521026-48-victim412" type="surname" value="Howard"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17521026-48-victim412" type="given" value="Ann"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17521026-48-victim412" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17521026-48-off247 t17521026-48-victim412"></join>
                     </persName>
                      
                  , <rs id="t17521026-48-viclabel248" type="occupation">spinster</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17521026-48-victim412 t17521026-48-viclabel248"></join>, with force and arms, and menaces, did make an assault, with an intent the money of the said Ann to steal, take, &amp;c
            </rs>. <rs id="t17521026-48-cd249" type="crimeDate">Sept. 21</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17521026-48-off247 t17521026-48-cd249"></join>. ++</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17521026-48-person413">
                  Ann 
                  Howard 
               <interp inst="t17521026-48-person413" type="surname" value="Howard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17521026-48-person413" type="given" value="Ann"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17521026-48-person413" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On Thursday the 21st of September, about nine at night, I and my sister Sarah were stopped by the prisoner in <rs id="t17521026-48-cd250" type="crimeDate">Grosvenor Street</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17521026-48-off247 t17521026-48-cd250"></join>. He said, Ladies, deliver your money, or I'll blow your brains out. He had a stick in his hand, but did not hold it up. My sister ran down street, and called out for help. Then the prisoner said as before, and put his hand to his pocket. I told him I would deliver my money presently, and immediately called out, Murder and thieves! He ran away, and I after him, calling out as I ran. 
               <persName id="t17521026-48-person414">
                  Richard 
                  Bumstead 
               <interp inst="t17521026-48-person414" type="surname" value="Bumstead"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17521026-48-person414" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17521026-48-person414" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             met him and stopped him. I was about seven yards from him at the time, and never lost light of him all the way; it was moonlight</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17521026-48-person415">
                  Sarah 
                  Howard 
               <interp inst="t17521026-48-person415" type="surname" value="Howard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17521026-48-person415" type="given" value="Sarah"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17521026-48-person415" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             confirmed the testimony of her sister, and was positive the prisoner was the man who stopped them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17521026-48-person416">
                  Richard 
                  Bumstead 
               <interp inst="t17521026-48-person416" type="surname" value="Bumstead"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17521026-48-person416" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17521026-48-person416" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             deposed to his taking the prisoner, and that the prosecutrix was near him at the time.  <rs id="t17521026-48-verdict251" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17521026-48-verdict251" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17521026-48-punish252" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17521026-48-punish252" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17521026-48-defend410 t17521026-48-punish252"></join>
               
                     <note>[Transportation. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
